                <article class="point-section">
                    <h4 class="heading">Shipping and Delivery Policy.</h4>
                    <h5 class="point">1. Delivery Methods and Obligations</h5>
                    <p>We understand that the process of moving large indoor and outdoor furniture can be challenging, and we work hard to find the best option that will minimize shipping costs and maximize your convenience. The shipping methods we use depend on the type of furniture, destination and other factors. Although we do try to minimize shipping costs, please keep in mind that packing furniture for safe transportation and delivery can be expensive; however, proper care in the shipping process is critical to protect your investment in each of our Products. To facilitate a safe and easy motor freight delivery of your Product(s), you must ensure that (i) someone eighteen (18) years of age or older (and not a minor in the State of delivery location) is available to accept delivery, (ii) all obstacles (including without limitation snow) which may hinder delivery is removed or otherwise remedied, and (iii) the location in which you want your Product(s) placed is cleared of all other items and ready for delivery (i.e., we are not responsible for moving or removing any existing items to make space for your Product(s)). Please note that if you are not at the delivery address at the agreed time for delivery or if you for any reason refuse delivery, you will incur a re-delivery charge from the shipper (note that Cabinfield has no control over the policies of third party shippers). If you are shipping to a remote area or hard to access location, then additional fees may apply. We will charge credit card on file for any transaction or like fees or expenses. </p>
                    
                    <p><strong>Remote Areas:</strong> Remote areas and hard to access locations are defined as addresses in remote areas in the country, locations on islands, or those delivery addresses only accessible by ferry or where access is limited to specific time schedules. An example of this would be Martha's Vinyard.  Prior to placing your order, please be upfront with us if you are in a remote area because there will be an extra cost associated with your delivery and standard delivery charges do not apply.</p>
                    <p><strong>Certificate of Insurance:</strong> You agree that if a certificate of insurance (“COI”) is required any COI fees are extra. A COI is sometimes required by a building prior to allowing a business to deliver or perform a service there. It is specific to the building and tenant and must meet the building's liability limit requirements, list their specific certificate holders and contain various other specifics, thus each COI must be custom generated by our insurance department for each customer. Some require very high levels of liability or umbrella policies that we will not incur the expense to carry, and we again will offer curbside delivery to a 3rd party facilitator who, for an additional expense, will deliver to the building (these cases, of course, would not necessitate a COI fee). Most, though not all, COIs are required by buildings in the New York City area. Before you place your order, please let us know if you reside in an apartment building or condominium complex and if a COI is required, and provide us with a sample COI from your building management. In the event we are given less than 5 business days' notice of the need for a COI, your delivery will be delayed to allow time to process your COI.</p>
                   
                    <h5 class="point">2. Delivery Time</h5>
                    <p>Under normal circumstances, most of our Products customarily have been ready to ship within eight (8) weeks of placing your order, though delays due to a pandemic, acts of war, riots, sever weather, strikes, and supply chain issues can increase this “lead” time to a range of twelve (12) to fourteen (14) weeks. However, even these estimated times are variable and will change due to the volume of orders at any given time or other factors beyond our control. If you need to have your Product(s) delivered by certain time, you must indicate this clearly at the time of your order and we will try to determine whether we believe it will be realistic to meet such a deadline, but even then, we cannot guaranty delivery by any certain date. We are able to ship some of the Products labeled on our Website as “QuickShip” using shorter lead times, but again we cannot guarantee any specific delivery date and we are not responsible for any delays.  Gazebos and Playsets may be available for shipping sooner, and customarily take approximately three (3) to six (6) weeks to be ready for shipping. You acknowledge that we cannot guarantee that any Products you order will be delivered within any specific timeframe. In the event that we expect delivery delays on particular pieces, you will be notified as soon as we learn of such delays. Despite our efforts, we may encounter circumstances beyond our control, and we may not meet our projected delivery schedule. For instance, to ensure the safety of customers and shippers, we reserve the right to delay deliveries due to hazardous road and/or weather conditions. In the occasions where delays may occur, we will do our very best to fill your order as expeditiously as possible, but we cannot guarantee an exact delivery date and are not responsible for monetary losses that may result from such unexpected delays. Unless otherwise determined by us, we will notify you by email (to your email of record) when the Product(s) you have