                    <h5 class="point">3. Indoor Furniture</h5>
                    <p>Our indoor furniture Products are typically delivered by a network of private shippers, and the shipper will be in touch with you to arrange a date and time for delivery. We offer two options for the delivery of our indoor furniture Products, curbside delivery and indoor delivery, as follows:</p>
                    <p>(a) <u>Standard Curbside Delivery:</u> The shipper will unload your Product(s) off the truck and place it on the sidewalk or otherwise in front of the delivery premises. This option is the least costly and is most often selected by our customers. If you select this delivery option, it will be your responsibility to inspect the Product(s) in the location (and note any issues in writing <u>before</u> signing to accept the delivery) it is placed and to move it onwards from such a location. Please note that the driver is an employee of the shipping company and not of Cabinfield. The driver may leave once the shipment is off the truck and you sign to accept delivery. The driver is not required to assist you in bringing the item into your home.</p>
                    
                    <p>(b) <u>Indoor Delivery and Setup:</u> For an additional fee, Cabinfield offers an indoor delivery and setup option where the shipper will take care of the entire unloading and set-up process. Please be sure the furniture will fit in the desired room and through all entryways and hallways within a comfortable margin. We are not responsible for any damage that may result from limited maneuverability due to narrow halls, stairwells, doors, etc. In the event that setup in your desired area is not feasible, the delivery and setup will occur in the closest reasonably accessible area in the delivery premises. If the Product(s) will need to be taken up more than one flight of stairs, <u>you must notify us of this in writing</u> before delivery occurs.</p>
                    
                    <h5 class="point">4. Outdoor Furniture</h5>
                    <p>While many of our outdoor Products are small enough to be shipped via UPS or FedEx, our larger outdoor patio furniture Products as well as our outdoor structures are delivered by motor freight. If the delivery location is not accessible by delivery truck (e.g., the truck is too large to enter your street), we will transport your furniture to the nearest reasonably accessible point, and it will be your responsibility to inspect and move the Product(s) at and from that location. When a Product(s) is delivered by common carrier motor freight, it will be your responsibility to move the Product(s) from the rear of the truck. You will need to make accommodations to assist the driver with unloading, and although most drivers are very accommodating and will help with the unloading (usually for a nominal additional fee), we cannot guarantee that your driver will be willing to provide such a service.</p>
                    
                    <h5 class="point">5. Inspection of Delivered Products</h5>
                    <p>For clarity and notwithstanding anything stated herein to the contrary, you are exclusively responsible for inspecting each Product(s) delivered at the time of delivery (<u>and before the driver has left the premises</u>) to make sure that it is in perfect condition. If you notice any issue and in order to obligate Cabinfield to remedy any damage or defects, you must note all such issues with specificity on the delivery confirmation sheet you sign and then immediately contact us. If you have any additional questions concerning shipment of your order, please call us at 866-450-9663 (WOOD).</p>
