                    <p>In the event that you communicate to us (directly or through a lack of responsiveness) that you are unable to accept the Product(s) you have ordered once your order is ready to ship, Cabinfield will hold the Product(s) for you, free of charge (as a courtesy), for a maximum period of four (4) weeks. After that four (4) week period has elapsed, unless other arrangements have been made and confirmed in writing (including by email) by Cabinfield, Cabinfield shall arrange for the continued storage of such Product(s) at your sole risk and expense. This may include, and you will be liable for, any and all fees and costs arising from such delay, including without limitation all of our own and all third-party fees and costs relating to storage, insurance, transport and other handling of such Product(s). If not otherwise agreed in writing by you and us, the costs for storage shall be the greater of (a) Two Hundred Fifty Dollars ($250) per month, or (b) five percent 5% of full invoice amount of the order for such Product(s) per month. Further, in the event that you do not arrange for delivery of the Product(s) within three (3) months of the originally scheduled delivery date, then Cabinfield shall be entitled (as determined by Cabinfield in its sole discretion) to (a) continue storing the Product(s) at your sole expense, or (b) resell or otherwise determine the use of any or all of the Product(s) ordered by you; provided, however, that Cabinfield will endeavor to give you no less than fourteen (14) calendar days advance written notification of our decision to resell or otherwise use the Product(s). For the sake of clarity, in any such circumstance Cabinfield shall also keep the full amount of any deposit already paid by you.</p>
